But at that time, monks, the great river Ganges was rolling along full up,
level to the banks. Then, monks, the Tathâgata went up to the boatman to
be carried across to the other bank. He said, ‘Gàutama, give me the fee
for crossing.’ ‘My good man.' replied the Tathâgata, ‘I have not the
fee for crossing.’ So saying, he went from that bank to the other bank on
a path through the sky.
